headline: 3 Consumer Stocks Skating on Thin Ice
summary: The performance of consumer discretionary businesses is closely linked to economic cycles. Over the past six months, it seems like demand trends are working against their favor as the industry has tumbled by 12.3%. This drop was significantly worse than the S&P 500’s 2.1% decline.
